item.dc:creator: @Speljohan Speljohan
item.description:
@Speljohan wrote:

[quote=“mwiebelhaus, post:17, topic:361222”][quote author=Speljohan link=topic=457510.msg3348797#msg3348797 date=1285065325]

[quote author=mwiebelhaus link=topic=457510.msg3348588#msg3348588 date=1285034826]

I’m disgusted by the fact that Sharia law is being enforced by muslims in Sweden, rather than respecting Sweden’s laws.
Personally I’d see to it that any practitioners of sharia law in Australia were deported, if I could. Sweden doesn’t need that shit either.
[/quote]It isn’t really being enforced, but in the slum cops can’t do shit at the moment. This is why SD got elected into the government. It doesn’t really bother me much at all, what bothers me is that the right-wing won, and in the coming 4 years they will turn our welfare into void. Say hello to the new Sweden, a clone of usa!

Its about time they get off their asses and back to work.
[/quote]You are clearly fukken clueless. Welfare doesn’t mean that nobody works, it means that our living standards are very high.

People who need welfare are fucking lazy. Both my grandparents worked in a grocery store and worked their asses off while raising three children. They retired at 40 and put all 3 children through college, now they own a shit load of land and make 100K+ a year from managing their land. Morale of the story? People who need welfare aren’t working “fukken” hard enough.

Ford the record I supprot unemployment checks, but not for people who have been out of a job for over a year, and they should have to show proof that they have been looking for a job, not just sitting and waiting until the year is up.

Also, I welfare programs are fine when the government isn’t running them or paying them, like non-profit organizations, this way I can write it off on my taxes, instead of getting taxed.[/quote]I mean welfare as in high living standards moron, not as in free money. It is our welfare system that is the backbone keeping us as one of the best countries in the world.
